title: Search for Abbey Lewis of Saltcoats who may have met man | Daily Mail Online
text: Police are searching for a missing girl, 16, who is feared to have left home to meet a man in his 40s who she met online Abbey Lewis, 16, has been missing from home since late on Sunday evening Family fear she may have met an older man online and was going to meet him Her sister revealed they believe she may have gone to the Birmingham area Published: 12:46 GMT, 28 February 2017 | Updated: 13:07 GMT, 28 February 2017 7 shares comments Police are searching for a missing Scottish teenage girl who may have travelled to England to meet an older man she met online. Abbey Lewis, 16, was last seen at around 11.15pm on Sunday in Dockhead Street in Saltcoats, North Ayrshire, heading in the direction of the train station. It is thought the teenager, who is from Saltcoats, may have been heading to the Birmingham area to meet someone she met on the internet. Abbey Lewis, 16, was last seen at around 11.15pm on Sunday in Dockhead Street in Saltcoats Her family reported her missing to police on Monday. Her sister Samantha Smith wrote online: 'She's missing from last night. Apparently a 40 year old guy came up from Birmingham to pick her up at Saltcoats train station late last night and we believe she has went back down with him. 'She hasn't been in contact with anyone since last night. She's 16 and a vulnerable young girl and we're very worried about her.' RELATED ARTICLES
